242011扫一扫下载界面新闻APP其他途径关注界面…意大利封城令提前泄露：民众“大逃亡”，警察医护火车站蹲守“法令午夜就生效了，快点！”安晶 · 2020/03/09 19:14浏览 33.7w来源：界面新闻字体：宋图片来源：半岛电视台。
/ [^ # 39 ^ # 105 ^ # 105 ^ # 105 ^ # 105 ^ # 105 ^ # 105 ^ # 105 ^ # 105 ^ # 105 ^ # 105 ^ # 105 ^ # 105 ^ # 105 ^ # 105 ^ # 105] / n. "Anjing 2020 / 03 / 09 19: 14 Browse 33.7 w http: / / www.jazeera
记者 | 安晶。
Reporter & # 124; Anjing.
“我正在中世纪城市帕多瓦吃晚饭时，短信和电话蜂拥而至：最后一趟火车晚上11点31分出发，在军队封路之前赶回罗马。
"I was having dinner in the medieval city of Padua when text messages and phone calls poured in: the last train left at 11: 31 pm to get back to Rome before the army closed the road.
‘法令午夜就生效了，快点！’”。
The decree goes into effect at midnight. Hurry up!
美联社记者托马斯（Trisha Thomas）记录了她赶在意大利政府封城前，于3月7日晚上与女儿从意大利北部威尼托大区赶回首都罗马的曲折经历。
Associated Press correspondent Trisha Thomas chronicles her tortuous journey from the northern Italian region of Veneto to the capital, Rome, on the night of March 7, ahead of the Italian government's closure.
。
.
截至8日晚，意大利的新冠病毒肺炎感染确诊已经增至7375例，死亡366例。
The number of confirmed cases of Newcastle virus pneumonia in Italy rose to 7,375 and 366 by the end of the night.
在24小时内，死亡人数暴涨了57%。
Within 24 hours, the death toll soared by 57 per cent.
。
.
8日凌晨，意大利政府公布新法令，规定从8日起，除工作特殊原因及紧急状况，禁止出入伦巴第大区及分布在威尼托、艾米利亚-罗马涅、皮埃蒙特和马尔凯大区的14个省。
In the early morning hours of August 8, the Italian Government issued a new decree prohibiting access to the Lombardy region and 14 provinces in the regions of Veneto, Emilia Romagna, Piedmont and Marquez, with the exception of special reasons for work and emergencies.
封城持续到4月3日，涉及1600多万人。
The closure lasted until 3 April and involved more than 16 million people.
。
.
然而，意大利媒体早在7日下午就得知了封城的消息；此时，政府还未签署封城法令。
However, the Italian media as early as the 7th afternoon to learn of the closure of the city; at this time, the government has not signed the decree.
。
.
媒体将封城的消息提前曝光后，引发了意大利北部地区民众的“大逃亡”。
Media coverage of the closure led to a "exodus" of northern Italians.
85%的确诊和超过90%的死亡病例都出现在伦巴第、艾米利亚-罗马涅和威尼托大区。
Eighty-five per cent of the cases diagnosed and over 90 per cent of the deaths occurred in the regions of Lombardy, Emilia Romagna and Veneto.
。
.
北部重灾区的民众乘火车或自驾车赶在法令生效之前逃往意大利南部，而南部地区的警察和医务人员则提前在火车站蹲守，准备对来自北部疫区的乘客进行检查登记。
Police and medical personnel from the north, who fled to southern Italy by train or by car before the law came into force, were crouched ahead of schedule at train stations to check on passengers arriving from northern affected areas.
。
.
托马斯就是逃亡大军中的一员。
Thomas was one of the fugitives.
。
.
据托马斯所述，在收到朋友催她赶快返回罗马的短信之前，她与女儿正在帕多瓦喝酒。
According to Thomas, she was drinking with her daughter in Padua before receiving a text message from friends urging her to hurry back to Rome.
之后，两人还分别与朋友聚餐。
After that, the two also had separate meals with friends.
帕多瓦距威尼斯约半小时车程，并不在意大利此前发布的封城令范围内。
Padua is about half an hour's drive from Venice, and is not part of Italy's previous edict.
。
.
看到朋友发来的警告后，托马斯与女儿立刻在网上订好火车票，开始赶往火车站。
Seeing the warning from his friend, Thomas and his daughter immediately booked their train tickets online and began to make their way to the station.
。
.
“在火车站，人们拖着巨大的行李，匆忙地通过进站口。
"At the train station, people were rushing past the entrance with their huge bags.
一些在售票机上买票的人脸上戴着口罩，手上还戴着橡胶手套。
Some people who buy tickets at the ticket machine wear masks on their faces and rubber gloves on their hands.
他们看上去跟我一样紧张，让我想起了从西贡（越南战争时期）飞出的最后一班飞机。
They looked as nervous as I was, reminding me of the last flight out of Saigon.
”。
"
火车进站后，相比往常的井然有序，托马斯看到“乘客们匆匆踏上台阶、推搡着上车”。
As the train pulled into the station, Thomas saw "passengers hurrying up the steps, pushing and shoving into the car" than usual.
托马斯与女儿买了预定席车票，有座位可座，很多没有座位的乘客只能挤在过道上，把行李放在地上，坐在行李上。
Thomas and his daughter bought reserved tickets, seats were available, and many unseated passengers packed into the aisles, left their luggage on the floor and sat on their luggage.
。
.
托马斯与女儿所在的包厢为六人座。
Thomas and his daughter were in a box for six.
包厢里的其他乘客都戴着口罩，或者用围巾捂着脸，还有人拿出免洗消毒液给大家用。
The other passengers in the box were wearing masks or mufflers covering their faces, and others had taken out disinfectant for everyone to use.
有的乘客则不停地刷手机，想知道到底发生了什么。
Some passengers kept brushing their phones to find out what was going on.
。
.
“没有检票员来检票，没有人问问题。
"There were no ticket inspectors to check the tickets and no questions.
四周异常安静、憋闷。
It was very quiet and stuffy around.
”。
"
由于紧张和担忧，托马斯整晚失眠，当她与女儿抵达罗马已经是八个小时之后。
Because of nervousness and worry, Thomas had insomnia all night, eight hours after she and her daughter arrived in Rome.
到家后，她与女儿开始了14天的隔离。
When she got home, she and her daughter began a 14-day quarantine.
。
.
在托马斯开始隔离之时，北部民众的逃亡也引发了南部地区的不满。
As Thomas began to segregate, the exodus from the north also sparked resentment in the south.
。
.
意大利东南部普利亚大区主席埃米利亚诺（Michele Emiliano）在社交媒体发文，呼吁北部的民众不要逃往南部，“停下来、回去”。
Michele Emiliano, president of Italy's south-eastern region of Puglia, sent a message on social media, calling on people in the north not to flee to the south and "stop, go back."
。
.
埃米利亚诺呼吁伦巴第、艾米利亚-罗马涅和威尼托大区的民众不要把病毒带到普利亚，“你们正在把病毒带向你们的兄弟姐妹、祖父祖母、叔叔、表亲和父母”。
Emiliano calls on the people of Lombardy, Emilia Romagna and Veneto not to bring the virus to Puglia. "You are taking the virus to your brothers and sisters, grandparents, uncles, cousins and parents."
。
.
意大利南部葡萄酒产区卡拉布里亚大区的主席桑特利（Jole Santelli）也加入抗议的行列，将北部民众涌向南部称为“疯狂”，呼吁意大利政府阻止民众出逃。
Jole Santelli, president of the region of Calabria, a wine-producing region in southern Italy, joined the protests, calling northern populations "crazy" to the south and calling on the Italian government to prevent people from fleeing.
。
.
西西里、拉齐奥等地已经要求从北部疫区返回的民众先自行隔离14天；在坎帕尼亚大区的萨莱诺，身穿防护服的警察和医生则在火车站蹲守。
Sicily, Lazio and others have asked people returning from the north to remain isolated for 14 days; in Saleno, Campania, police and doctors in protective clothing are crouching at railway stations.
。
.
面对意大利的升级防控，多地监狱还发生了骚乱。
Riots broke out in many of Italy's jails in the face of escalating control.
得知政府取消探视之后，萨莱诺、那不勒斯、弗罗西诺内和摩德纳的监狱爆发骚乱，摩德纳的骚乱还造成三名囚犯死亡。
On learning of the cancellation of visits by the Government, riots broke out in the prisons of Saleno, Naples, Frosinone and Modena, and three prisoners died as a result of the riots in Modena.
。
.
总理孔特已经对封城令提前泄露表示了谴责，他指责此举在民众中制造了“不安全感和混乱，不能容忍”。
Prime Minister Conte has condemned the early disclosure of the edict, accusing it of creating "insecurity and chaos and intolerance" among the population.
。
.
参与签署法令的部分科学家则推测，封城令可能是孔特在将法令草案送给各大区主席征求意见时泄露的。
Some of the scientists who signed the decree speculated that it might have been leaked by Conte when he sent the draft decree to the regional chairmen for comments.
。
.
封城后的米兰。
Milan after the siege.
图片来源：Twitter。
Source: Twitter.
由于确诊病例激增，伦巴第大区等地的医疗系统正面临巨大压力。
The health-care system, including in the Lombardy region, is under enormous pressure as a result of the sharp increase in confirmed cases.
伦巴第大区应急部门的负责人佩森提（Antonio Pesenti）在接受路透社采访时警告，当地的医疗系统距离崩溃仅“一步之遥”。
Antonio Pesenti, head of the emergency department in Lombardy, warned in an interview with Reuters that the local health-care system was "only a step away" from collapse.
。
.
佩森提指出，由于空间不够，医院已经在过道、康复室、手术室等一切可用的地方设立重症监护设施。
Because of lack of space, the hospital has set up intensive care facilities in all available areas, such as aisles, convalescent rooms and operating theatres, he said.
部分医院则完全腾空，专门用于收治重症病人。
Some hospitals have been completely emptied and used exclusively for the treatment of seriously ill patients.
。
.
与佩森提的焦虑截然相反的是，在米兰等地，部分民众依然对疫情没有紧张感。
In contrast to Pessendi's anxieties, in places like Milan, some people are still not nervous about the outbreak.
周末，由于天气晴好，米兰郊区的滑雪场吸引了大量游客。
On weekends, thanks to the fine weather, the ski resort in the suburbs of Milan attracts a lot of tourists.
。
.
米兰市长萨拉（Beppe Sala）已经呼吁米兰市民改变生活方式，“我们需要避免一切不必要的接触，请你们尽可能留在家中”，“现在最重要的事是每个人都待在家中”。
Beppe Sala, Milan's mayor, has called on Milan's citizens to change their way of life, "we need to avoid all unnecessary contact, please stay home as much as possible," and "the most important thing is for everyone to stay at home."
。
.
根据新法令要求，封城地区的电影院、博物馆、剧院、健身房、游泳池和滑雪场将全部关闭。
Cinemas, museums, theatres, gymnasiums, swimming pools and ski resorts in the closed areas will all be closed under the new law.
。
.
但餐馆和酒吧依然能从早上6点到下午6点开放，前提是需保证每名顾客之间的间隔至少有一米。
But restaurants and bars are still open from 6am to 6pm, provided that there is at least one meter interval between each customer.
。
.
封城区的公共交通还将继续运行。
Public transport will continue to operate in the urban areas.
。
.
